<DOC><DOCNO> AP890611-0010 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-11-89 1138EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Mozambique-Fighting     06-11 0170</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Mozambique-Fighting,0175</SECOND><HEAD>Government Says Troops Kill 44 Rebels</HEAD><DATELINE>MAPUTO, Mozambique (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Government soldiers killed 44 rebelfighters during a battle in the southern province of Gaza, thenational news agency AIM reported Sunday.   The rebels of the Mozambique National Resistance were killedwhile attempting to attack a military training center Friday in thetown of Machubane, AIM said, citing a statement by Col. ErnestoBulele.   Machubane is about 120 miles northeast of the capital of Maputo.   The report gave no additional details and made no mention ofgovernment troop casualties. Information on the fighting is oftensketchy and can take days or even weeks to reach Maputo.   The rebels have been fighting since 1977 in a bid to undermineMozambique's Marxist government.   The rebels have devastated the economy of the southeast Africannation with hit-and-run attacks on both military and civiliantargets.   Mozambique is one of the poorest countries in the world and anestimated 6 million of its 15 million people are in need of food aid.</TEXT></DOC>